cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CR

This paper deals with a computer vision problem of multi-target multi-camera (MTMC) tracking and re-identification of vehicles in urban traffic. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning models and optimization techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also mentions the use of AI for traffic optimization, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible category. The paper also involves robotics and control, which makes cs.RO (Robotics) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the security and privacy implications of using traffic cameras, which makes cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a possible category.
